# World_Design

## 1. Applies when
Open world, semi-open world, large-map exploration, or regions / POI / paths /
density are important.

## 2. This document owns
World structure; region divisions; POI types; path networks; exploration density;
event-mount rules; resource-point distribution; world-state outward signs.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Event body text; mission choices/consequences; full quest chains; character
dialogue.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. World positioning · 3. Regions · 4. POI types ·
5. Paths & navigation · 6. Exploration density · 7. World-state presentation ·
8. Event-mount rules · 9. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- World vs Mission — where and density vs content.
- World vs Level — large-map structure vs a single playable space.
- World vs Resource — resource-point distribution vs resource rules.

## 6. Common audit rules
- No event body text in World (WORLD-NO-EVENT-BODY check).
- Use `stop_at: "[migrated]"` boundary checks for legacy content.
- Event-mount rules reference Mission, do not duplicate.
